Program: The History Hour
Title: Dickey Chapelle - War Reporter
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p04dl2c6
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 6 Nov 2016
On this week's programme, how pioneering American woman war reporter, Dickey Chapelle, was killed in Vietnam; plus two very different perspectives on Mao's China, Mexican writer Octavio Paz and the escape which made Harry Houdini's name. PHOTO: Dickey Chapelle during a US Marines operation in 1958 (Credit: US Marine Corps / Associated Press) Show less